summary: “Imagine going into a book shop and Peter reciting poetry because he doesn’t know how else to tell you he loves you. “We should...
body:
“Imagine going into a book shop and Peter reciting poetry because he doesn’t know how else to tell you he loves you.

“We should go.” You smiled putting down your text book as Peter gave you a look of pure confusion. “Like right now? We need to study.” He stammered putting his pen down “Finals are a month away, and we’ve only been studying four nights a week and-” you leaned over closing his own text book. “Peter do you hear yourself? we have a month, and we both already know these topics inside out! we’ve got this!” he scoffed opening his book again, only for you to close it. “Peter, you’ve got this.” He gazed at you, mouth opening to say something only to stop smiling at you.

“Okay, where do you want to go?” He leaned back briefly glancing out the window. “It’s raining.” “So.” he chuckled piling the books up. “So, we’ll get soaked.” you smiled chucking an umbrella at him. “look at that, its almost as if it stops you from getting wet.” he laughed standing up. “okay, but where are we going?” You smiled raising your eyebrows, swaying on your feet. “Book shop?” he smiled “book shop.” throwing on your coat and tossing him his he kept smiling, it was gentle you loved his smile. The way his eyes would crinkle and he tucked his hands in his jean pockets. that damn smile.

“Where else do we go?” he asked as you both bounded down the steps and on to the street. “Is there anywhere else you’d like to go?” you laughed looking at him, he’d grown since high school. You were still getting used to not being on eye level with him, a part of you liked it. “No. It’s our spot.” He said raising his eyebrows at you lips pouting into a funny face, you laughed linking arms to keep under the umbrella he was holding. You felt him tense up, checking his face he looked down. His cheeks were pink, you kept thinking about when he was going to ask you out. You got that he was shy, you loved that about him but you both knew how you felt. 

Arriving at the book shop you scoped around, eyeing all the shelves. “Which ones don’t you have?” He smiled and you stuck your you stuck your tong out. “I know what I want” You smiled scanning the poetry shelf. “You still not managed to find that Shelly book?” he smiled helping you look. “No” you sighed sitting at a table pulling out another book in stead. “I just need to get something.” looking up you caught Peter, your face still a grey cloud. “what!?” He sighed smiling. You kept pouting. “I’ve looked in every book shop in Queens Pete.” you sighed. “Maybe you should get it online.” He said as you rest your face in your arms. Muffling a maybe Peter walked to the counter. 

Hearing light steps you sighed, “Don’t try and scare me, at this point its just cruel.” You muffled not looking up. “The mountains mingle with the river, and the rivers with the ocean; the winds of heaven mix forever, with a sweet emotion,” You knew that poem “nothing in the world is single, all things by law divine, in one another’s being mingle, why not I with thine?” You looked up shocked as Peter leaned on the shelf a smile playing on his lips. you stood up and went to get the book from his hands only for him to move to the other side “See! How the mountains kiss high heaven, and the waves clasp one another; no sister flower would be forgiven if it disdained its brother; and the sunlight claps the earth, and the moonbeams kiss the sea” you stood in front of him, your smile growing wider as he stopped reading and passed you the book. “What are all these kissing’s worth, if thou kiss not me?” you both stood there looking at each other. grabbing his jaw you pulled him in kissing him, you could both feel yourselves smiling into the kiss. It was warm and gentle just like him. Pulling back you pushed his hair out of his face. “I love you.” You smiled stepping back lightly hitting him with the book. “Took you long enough.” you smiled taking his hand. “But was it worth it?” he said kissing your forehead. “Of course.”

title: Arrows and gunshots
body:
read it on the AO3 at https://ift.tt/2M0ranr

by smile_it_will_get_better

Tony decided that he should start a club. Maybe he’d call it the “2am Therapy for idiot’s club”.

Tony always thought that he was the only one in the tower with a fucked-up sleep schedule, but then again he was surrounded by weirdos so why was he even surprised? His little 2am adventures used to be done alone, in the large empty tower with no one to see him. Now he found himself sometimes crossing paths with the occupants of the tower, and every time it weirded him out. He’d seen Steve many times around, Bruce was always in his lab at any hour of the day, Natasha was just Natasha, and Thor only slept when convenient. (He also slept naked and absolutely everywhere. Not that Tony noticed or anything.)

The one-person Tony had never met on his 2am travels was Clint. Tony just assumed that the spy was very good at keeping hidden, or he had an actual normal sleep schedule. He did seem the most normal out of them all, on a good day of course. So, to say Tony was surprised to see the archer out late was an understatement.

by smile_it_will_get_better

Tony decided that he should start a club. Maybe he’d call it the “2am Therapy for idiot’s club”.

Tony always thought that he was the only one in the tower with a fucked-up sleep schedule, but then again he was surrounded by weirdos so why was he even surprised? His little 2am adventures used to be done alone, in the large empty tower with no one to see him. Now he found himself sometimes crossing paths with the occupants of the tower, and every time it weirded him out. He’d seen Steve many times around, Bruce was always in his lab at any hour of the day, Natasha was just Natasha, and Thor only slept when convenient. (He also slept naked and absolutely everywhere. Not that Tony noticed or anything.)

The one-person Tony had never met on his 2am travels was Clint. Tony just assumed that the spy was very good at keeping hidden, or he had an actual normal sleep schedule. He did seem the most normal out of them all, on a good day of course. So, to say Tony was surprised to see the archer out late was an understatement.

summary:
So now that I've slightly moved past my Grief^TM caused by Infinity War I am having a thought
Considering Thanos' goal revolves...
body:
So now that I’ve slightly moved past my Grief^TM caused by Infinity War I am having a thought

Considering Thanos’ goal revolves around preserving natural resources, and he has a bejeweled gauntlet that gives him the power of God^TM he literally picked the fuckin’ least effective solotion available to him.

Like, sure, commiting universal genocide will get the job done, but for how long tho? It’s not gonna stop everyone from breeding, my dude, populations will be back to thier old numbers in no time; then what? Is it gonna be the same song and dance? How many times os he gonna do that until he just wipes out everyone?

Like just off the top of my head - super tired and with a half dense brain-fog going on - just like. Extend the universe’s resource capacity? Make it biologically impossible to have more than x amount of offspring? Reduce the amount of resources necissary to sustain an individual? If he can wipe half the universe out of existence with the snap of his fingers all those seem plausable, right? And it would just be so much more efficient, in my opinion.
